%%TITLE: NOVA: Nested Observation Verification for Long-Context Reranking
%%AUTHORS: Mira Chen; Diego Alvarez; Priya Shah
%%VENUE: Workshop on Reliable Agentic Retrieval
%%YEAR: 2026
%%TOPIC: long-context reranking and evidence verification
%%ABSTRACT_START
NOVA studies how long-context rerankers can verify evidence spans while operating over millions of candidate documents. The paper introduces nested observation checks that reduce spurious relevance matches without requiring a separate index.
%%ABSTRACT_END
1 Introduction
Long-context retrieval systems are increasingly used by autonomous agents to select evidence from large workspaces. We focus on evidence verification and failure modes induced by incomplete observations.
2 Method
The model receives candidate document clusters, source snippets, and rubric constraints. It predicts both a ranking and a compact evidence ledger for downstream audit.
